  <static seed="27" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/FractionArithmetic/MultiplyFractions10.pg">
    <statement><p>Multiply: <m>\displaystyle{ \frac{5}{9} \cdot \frac{1}{9} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{5}{81}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To multiply two fractions, simply multiply both numerators and both denominators. We have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   \frac{5}{9} \cdot \frac{1}{9}
           \amp = \frac{5 \cdot 1}{9 \cdot 9} \\
           \amp = \frac{5}{81}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>The answer to this question is <m>\displaystyle{\frac{5}{81}}</m>.</p>
</solution>
